\ === REGIME CCCCC — predictive-only loss also fails on NSUM benchmark ===
\
\ L23 = PredError + alpha * (K/n) + gamma * DegeneracyPenalty
\   gamma = 0.1, alpha grid {0.01, 0.1, 1}, gamma fixed pre-commit.
\   PASS evaluated by PredError (NOT L23) per user spec.
\
\ Per-alpha aggregate:
\
\   alpha    pred_wins   mean_delta_pred   concentrated   winners
\   0.01     2/6         +0.00082          TRUE           path, ER_n10_p30
\   0.1      0/6         -0.00189          --             (none)
\   1.0      0/6         -0.00553          --             (none)
\
\ Best alpha = 0.01 (pred_wins=2, mean_delta=+0.00082).
\ Concentrated = TRUE -> wins confined to C22-winners.
\
\ Pre-reg classifier:
\   AAAAA requires pred_wins>=4, mean_delta>0.005, NOT concentrated.
\   BBBBB requires pred_wins>=3, NOT has_K1.
\   CCCCC: pred_wins<=2 OR concentrated OR mean_delta<=0 OR has_K1.
\
\   Best alpha has pred_wins=2 AND concentrated=TRUE -> CCCCC fires.
\
\ CRITICAL DIAGNOSTIC: delta_spread across alphas = +0.00635.
\ Non-trivial alpha-sensitivity -> landscape has structure but search
\ cannot find groups beating degree.  Strongly suggests degree IS
\ the oracle for NSUM dynamics (a_{t+1} = normalize(A * a_t)).
\
\ Three families of loss tested on same 6 substrates, all fail:
\   L21 = MDL only             -> CCC   (cycle 21)
\   L22 = MDL + lambda*Pred    -> CCCC  (cycle 22)
\   L23 = Pred + alpha*K/n     -> CCCCC (this cycle)
\
\ Six substrates, three loss families, three failures vs degree.
\ The honest interpretation per user spec (2026-05-23):
\
\   degree IS sufficient statistic for NSUM-update dynamics being
\   predicted; no fixed-loss + fixed-primitive STEP-CA optimizer
\   can beat it on these substrates because the benchmark is
\   degree-biased.
\
\ NEW DIRECTION (user pivot 2026-05-23):
\   Move from "test L candidates on fixed primitives" to
\   "engine that evolves its own primitive alphabet via formal
\   induction protocol: DISCOVER -> SPECIFY -> FREEZE -> TEST ->
\   PROMOTE -> RETEST -> ATTEST."
\
\ Phase A (this demo) closes the loss-family arc on the original
\ NSUM benchmark.  Phase B (cycle 24+) opens primitive induction
\ as the next architectural test.
\
\ CATALOGUE UPDATE:
\   - Substrate-distinguishing positives:    2 (matryoshka c18, L-monotonic c19/20)
\   - Modest narrow signals:                 2
\   - Substrate-derived NEGATIVES:           4 (HEDGE3 c12C, MDL c21,
\                                              MDL+Pred c22, Pred-only c23A)
\   - Substrate ~ classical:                 3
\   - Retracted/narrowed:                   10
\
\ Honest scope: loss-family hypothesis on NSUM benchmark is
